TI  - Multinational Enterprises and Public Policy
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 115
EP  - 136
VL  - 29
IS  - 1
AB  - The interaction between governments and multinational enterprises is analyzed using a new conceptual framework. This captures the key aspects of Richard Caves′ “normative” and “behavioral” approaches to the literature, but also develops a more contemporary “strategic” approach. Our framework uses insights from the resource-based theory of the firm to analyze managerial aspects of multinational enterprises and public policy neglected by Caves. In particular, we incorporate strategies of national responsiveness.
